The New South Wales government has
sold some of the Australian stateâ€™s electricity assets for A$5.3
billion, the Sydney Morning Herald reported, citing an
announcement by Treasurer  Eric Roozendaal .  Electricity retailers Country Energy and Integral Energy,
and the output from power generator Eraring were sold to  Origin
Energy Ltd.  for A$3.3 billion, the newspaper said.  EnergyAustralia, the output from the Delta West generator,
the Mount Piper Extension and two Marulan development sites,
were all sold to the Hong Kong company TRUenergy Holdings Pty
Ltd. for A$2 billion, it reported.  Eight of 11 board members of two of the state's power
generators quit in protest, the Herald said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
